{
  "name": "Sol (Miners' Folly)",
  "description": "The real solar system, one difference: a mining rig drilled through Luna's crust and shorted its own capacitor. Nobody meant to change the Moon's orbit -- but the accidental jolt scaled Luna's orbital speed by +15%, exactly the way the game's own engine pulses ever ship's velocity. labs/12-oops-at-the-moon computed the honest consequence: a wider, more eccentric orbit (e~0.335, period ~50.6 days instead of ~27.3) whose perigee visibly oscillates under the Sun's pull over months -- degraded, but never close to threatening the atmosphere. This file approximates that new orbit as a circular rail at its semi-major axis (5.7816e8 m), since this engine's ephemeris only supports circular orbits; the real post-accident orbit the lab integrated is actually eccentric. The rig itself is still up there, in a low scrappy orbit everyone now calls Miners' Folly.",
